<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="637" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[713,1250,254,691]" box="[714,814,254,280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[713,1250,254,691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">
This genus has often been confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Thiele, 1934" authorityName=", Thiele" authorityYear="1934" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Microcardium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="THIELE J." box="[810,948,317,343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" pagination="779 - 1022" refId="ref12980" refString="THIELE J. 1934. - Handbuch der systematischen Weichtierkunde. Zweiter Band. DritterTeil. Scaphopoda. Bivalvia. Cephalopoda. Fischer, Stuttgart: 779 - 1022." type="book chapter" year="1934">Thiele, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="WILSON B. R. &amp; STEVENSON S. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="637" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref13088" refString="WILSON B. R. &amp; STEVENSON S. E. 1977. - Cardiidae (Mollusca, Bivalvia) of Western Australia. Western Australian Museum Special Publication 9: 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1977">Wilson &amp; Stevenson 1977</bibRefCitation>
), but it is quite distinct and can be easily characterised by its homogeneous outer sculpture with numerous radial ribs and spines developed on the whole surface (
<bibRefCitation author="POUTIERS J. - M." box="[919,1076,444,470]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" refId="ref12018" refString="POUTIERS J. - M. 1992. - The Australasian Protocardiinae" type="book" year="1992">Poutiers 1992</bibRefCitation>
). The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Noda, 1988" authorityName="Noda" authorityYear="1988" box="[714,951,475,501]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Tobarum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,809,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Tobarum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="NODA H." box="[817,951,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" pagination="29 - 85" refId="ref11880" refString="NODA H. 1988. - Molluscan fossils from the Ryukyu Islands, Southwest Japan. Part 2. Gastropoda and Pelecypoda from the Shinzato Formation in the middle part of Okinawa-jima. Science Reports of the Institute of Geosciences, University of Tsukuba (B) 9: 29 - 85." type="journal article" year="1988">Noda, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Noda, 1988" authorityName="Noda" authorityYear="1988" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Frigidocardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tobaruense" subGenus="T.">
<emphasis box="[1066,1085,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">F.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1100,1122,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">T.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1138,1247,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">tobaruense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="NODA H." box="[714,851,507,533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" pagination="29 - 85" refId="ref11880" refString="NODA H. 1988. - Molluscan fossils from the Ryukyu Islands, Southwest Japan. Part 2. Gastropoda and Pelecypoda from the Shinzato Formation in the middle part of Okinawa-jima. Science Reports of the Institute of Geosciences, University of Tsukuba (B) 9: 29 - 85." type="journal article" year="1988">Noda, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(a Pliocene species from 
<collectingRegion box="[1145,1247,507,533]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
Island, SW 
<collectingCountry box="[835,897,539,565]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Japan</collectingCountry>
), actually belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schneider 1995: 322)" baseAuthorityName="Schneider" baseAuthorityPageNumber="322" baseAuthorityYear="1995" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Microcardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1104,1247,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Microcardium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SCHNEIDER J. A." box="[721,953,570,596]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" pagination="321 - 346" refId="ref12653" refString="SCHNEIDER J. A. 1995. - Phylogeny of the Cardiidae (Mollusca, Bivalvia): Protocardiinae, Laevicardiinae, Lahilliinae, Tulongocardiinae subfam. n. and Pleuriocardiinae subfam. n. Zoologica Scripta 24 (4): 321 - 346." type="journal article" year="1995">Schneider 1995: 322</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[713,1250,254,691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Habe" authorityYear="1951" box="[737,903,602,628]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Frigidocardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cardiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="637" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[737,903,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="637">Frigidocardium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurrence is restricted to the tropical Indo-West Pacific, where it is known from the Miocene onwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
